claim.claim-text:
1. A method, comprising:
receiving, by at least one mobile device, an advertised Closed Subscriber Group (CSG) Identifier (ID) that identifies a CSG corresponding to a base station broadcast by a base station;
receiving, by the at least one mobile device, an advertised CSG indication that distinguishes between the base station permitting access to members of the CSG and permitting access to the members and non-members of the CSG broadcast by a base station;
identifying whether the advertised CSG ID matches one or more CSG IDs included in an allowed CSG list, stored in a memory of the at least one mobile device; and
generating a preference for selecting the base station as compared to a disparate base station when the advertised CSG indication specifies that the base station permits access to the members and the non-members of the CSG and the advertised CSG ID matches at least one of the one or more CSG IDs included in the allowed CSG list.

21. A computer program product, comprising:
a non-transitory computer-readable medium comprising:
code for causing at least one computer to receive an advertised Closed Subscriber Group (CSG) Identifier (ID) that identifies a CSG corresponding to a base station;
code for causing at least one computer to receive an advertised CSG indication that distinguishes between the base station permitting access to members of the CSG and permitting access to the members and non-members of the CSG;
code for causing at least one computer to identify whether the advertised CSG ID matches one or more CSG IDs included in an allowed CSG list, stored in a memory of the at least one computer; and
code for causing at least one computer to generate a preference for selecting the base station as compared to a disparate base station when the advertised CSG indication specifies that the base station permits access to the members and the non-members of the CSG and the advertised CSG ID matches at least one of the one or more CSG IDs included in the allowed CSG list.
